<p>A dietary supplement is "a product intended to supplement the diet that bears or contains one or more of the following ingredients: a vitamin; a mineral; an herb or other botanical; an amino acid; a dietary substance for use by man to supplement the diet by increasing the total dietary intake; and 'is not represented for use as a conventional food or as a sole item of a meal or the diet'."<br/><a title="(Federal Food, Drug and Cosmetic Act, Section 201 (ff))" href="http://www.fda.gov/opacom/laws/fdcact/fdcact1.htm">(Federal Food, Drug and Cosmetic Act, Section 201 (ff))</a></p>
<p>Dietary supplements are specific to all of the food labeling regulations as well as regulations specified to supplements. </p>
